  "prompt": "Which one is better: Royal Enfield Standard 350 or Classic 350?",
  "response": "Choosing between the Royal Enfield Standard 350 and the Classic 350 depends on various factors, including your personal preferences, riding style, and expectations from a motorcycle. Here\u2019s a comparison to help you decide which might be better for you:\n\n**Royal Enfield Standard 350:**\n- **Design:** The Standard 350 has a more utilitarian and minimalist design. It often appeals to riders who prefer a classic, no-frills look.\n- **Comfort:** Generally, it offers a straightforward riding experience with traditional ergonomics.\n- **Features:** It may lack some of the modern features found in the Classic 350 but is appreciated for its simplicity.\n- **Price:** Typically, the Standard 350 is priced lower than the Classic 350, making it an attractive option for budget-conscious buyers.\n- **Customization:** It serves as a good base for customization, allowing riders to personalize their bikes according to their preferences.\n\n**Royal Enfield Classic 350:**\n- **Design:** The Classic 350 is known for its vintage-inspired design with more attention to aesthetics. It includes features like chrome accents, a more polished look, and additional styling elements.\n- **Comfort:** It usually offers a more comfortable seat, better suspension setup, and ergonomic enhancements that contribute to a smoother ride.\n- **Features:** The Classic 350 tends to come with more modern features, such as improved instrumentation, better lighting, and sometimes additional tech like fuel injection.\n- **Price:** It is generally priced higher than the Standard 350 due to its enhanced features and design elements.\n- **Resale Value:** The Classic 350 often retains its value well, making it a good investment if you plan to sell it later.\n\n**Conclusion:**\n- **Choose the Standard 350 if:** You prefer a straightforward, budget-friendly motorcycle with a classic, utilitarian design and potential for customization.\n- **Choose the Classic 350 if:** You want a motorcycle with vintage aesthetics, additional comfort, and modern features, and are willing to invest a bit more for these enhancements.\n\nUltimately, the \"better\" bike depends on what you value more in a motorcycle. Both models offer the iconic Royal Enfield riding experience, so consider test riding both to see which one feels right for you.",
